{{Infobox film festival | name = Kyiv International Short Film Festival | image =Kyiv International Short Film Festival.png | location = {{flagicon|Ukraine}} [[Kiev]], [[Ukraine]] | founded = 2012 | date = April | language = International | website = http://www.kisff.org }}
'''Kyiv International Short Film Festival''' is an annual festival, held in [[Kiev]] and aimed to acquaint the audience with [[short film]]s from around the world. Latest movies, winners of international festivals, retrospectives of extraordinary figures and special attention to modern and classic [[Ukrainian cinema|Ukrainian movies]]. KISFF also organizes projects and events to develop a diversity of short films in [[Ukraine]]. [[File:Жопа Хэнка.webm|center|300px|thumb|Anti-clerical film «Kissing Hank's Ass» was shown on festival in 2015<ref>[http://ukrkino.com.ua/news/?id=1839 Українські учасники KISFF 2015]</ref><ref>[https://static1.squarespace.com/static/5343c8b5e4b01b8f6b79ddcc/t/56012003e4b0f36b5cabb00a/1442914307830/catalogue_KISFF_2015.pdf The 4th Kyiv International Short Film Festival]</ref>]]
== Jury == The festival jury is elected by administration of the festival. Usually, there are several foreign guests and representatives of Ukrainian cinema. The jury members are known directors, producers and filmmakers that have international awards in cinema industry.
