{{Infobox wildfire | title = Marshes Fire | image = | caption = | cost = | injuries = | fatalities = | reference = <ref name=cdf>{{cite web|title=Marshes Fire|url=http://www.fire.ca.gov/current_incidents/incidentdetails/Index/1454|website=[[CALFIRE]]|accessdate=October 11, 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160927131114/http://www.fire.ca.gov/current_incidents/incidentdetails/Index/1454|archivedate=September 27, 2016|df=}}</ref> <!-- ONLY FOR INDIVIDUAL FIRES --> | date = {{Start date|2016|9|26}} - {{End date|2016|9|29}} | location =[[Stanislaus National Forest]], [[Tuolumne County]], [[California]] | coordinates = {{coord|37.79635|-120.32484|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = USA California Northern | pushpin_map_caption = Location of fire in California | area = {{Convert| 1,080 |acre|km2|0}} | buildings = | cause = Vehicle parked in dry grass | landuse = | perps = | motive = }}
The '''Marshes Fire''' was a 2016 [[wildfire]] that burned just north of the [[Don Pedro Reservoir]] in [[Tuolumne County]], [[California]].<ref name=cdf/> The fire, which started on September 26, burned {{Convert| 1,080 |acre|km2|0}} of land from before being contained on October 4. Approximately 30 homes were evacuated and two minor injuries were reported.<ref>{{cite news|title=Marshes Fire in Sonoma County Fully Contained: Cal Fire|url=http://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/local/Marshes-Fire-in-Sonoma-County-Fully-Contained-Cal-Fire-395374341.html|accessdate=11 October 2016|work=NBC Bay Area|agency=[[NBC Bay Area]]|date=29 September 2016}}</ref>
==Effects== Over a dozen homes were evacuated in the Moccasin Ranch Estates subdivision during the first hours of the fire.<ref name=evacs>{{cite news|last1=McCarthy|first1=Guy|title=Marshes Fire cost $2.5 million so far|url=http://www.uniondemocrat.com/localnews/4699911-151/marshes-fire-cost-25-million-so-far|accessdate=11 October 2016|agency=[[The Union Democrat]]|date=29 September 2016}}</ref> [[Pacific Gas and Electric]] also reported a number of power outages due to the fire. The fire briefly threatened the [[Hetch Hetchy Reservoir|Hetch Hetchy Regional Water System]] headquarters, but normal water operations continued throughout the fire.<ref name=evacs/>
==Cause== On September 28, officials from [[Cal Fire]] released a statement saying that the fire had been started by a vehicle parked in dry grass.<ref name="cause">{{cite news|last1=Cowan|first1=Jason|title=Cal Fire releases cause of Marshes Fire|url=http://www.uniondemocrat.com/localnews/4696975-151/cal-fire-releases-cause-of-marshes-fire?referrer=carousel1|accessdate=11 October 2016|agency=[[The Union Democrat]]|date=28 September 2016}}</ref> Investigators determined that the driver, who had been traveling along Marshes Flat Road, pulled over to take a break and the fire started shortly thereafter.<ref name="cause"/> ==References==
