{{Infobox holiday |holiday_name = Rotiyaan ki eid/Rottela Panduga |type = religious |image = |imagesize = |caption = |official_name = |nickname = |observedby = |litcolor = |longtype = |significance = |begins = |ends = |date = <!-- Use next three if holiday is the same day of the same week every year --> |week_ordinal = <!-- "first", "second", "last", etc. --> |weekday = <!-- "Sunday", "Monday", "Friday", etc. --> |month = <!-- "January", "February", "December", etc. --> <!-- Use next three if the date changes in an unusual pattern each year --> |date2011 = <!-- only for days that change each year --> |date2012 = <!-- only for days that change each year --> |date2013 = <!-- only for days that change each year --> |celebrations = |duration=3 days |frequency=annual |observances = |relatedto = Islam ([[sufism]]/[[Barelvi]]) }} [[File:Rottela panduga.nellore.006.JPG|left|250px|Hindu-Muslim women Pilgrims exchanging Rotis,at svarana Tank,Nellore]] [[File:Rottela panduga -01-Nellore.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Women Pilgrims exchanging Rotis,at svarana Tank,Nellore]] [[File:Rottela panduga 011.JPG|thumb|right|250px|samtana ROti exchanging placeat svarana Tank, Nellore]] [[File:Rottela panduga 009.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Job Roti exchanging place at svarana Tank,Nellore]] '''Rotiyaan ki eid''' or '''Rottela Panduga''' is an annual three-day [[urs]](festival) held at [[Bara Shaheed Dargah]] in [[Nellore]] in [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]].<ref>http://www.deccanchronicle.com/channels/cities/regions/nellore/stage-set-rottela-panduga-640</ref><ref>http://www.hindu.com/2007/02/02/stories/2007020202410200.htm</ref> Annual event is observed in the month of [[Muharram]] as [[urs]] of 12 martyrs whose mortal remains are buried in the compound. Women who visit the shrine, exchange their [[roti]]s(flat breads) in Nellore Tank.<ref>http://www.mana-andhra.com/?p=41027 రొట్టెల పండుగ కు రాష్ట్ర స్థాయి గుర్తింపు</ref>
