{{Orphan|date=February 2009}} A '''warehouse bank''' account is a [[bank account]] at a regular [[commercial bank]] in which all clients’ [[capital (economics)|funds]] are commingled or pooled, for the purpose of concealing the client’s ownership of the funds. <ref name="USDOJ1">[http://www.usdoj.gov/tax/txdv04231.htm Scheme Involved Nevada Corporations, Bogus Insurance And Consulting Expenses, “Warehouse Bank,” And Offshore Credit Cards]</ref> <ref name="USDOJ2">[http://www.usdoj.gov/opa/pr/2008/April/08_tax_269.html Federal Court in Seattle Permanently Shuts Down “Warehouse Bank” Tax Defier Operation with $28 Million in Deposits over Four Years]</ref>
